cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as Muller games are a well-known topic in logic and automata theory. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a likely category as Muller games are a type of two-player game and this category covers research on game theory and its applications in computer science. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as Muller games involve algorithms for solving games on graphs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as Muller games can be used to model various AI problems such as planning and verification. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category but still possible as Muller games can be used to study the expressiveness of programming languages.
